I bought the full version several years ago, I loved it so much I bought it again when my original phone died. My favorite feature, and the main reason I purchased the app. is the great variety of wonderful, quality, live filters for photos and video. The macro and torch feature are also superb. My only complaint is an on-going issue with the app either failing to open, crashing within a minute of being opened, and most commonly; the app is stuck, unresponsive to anything (even to being turned off) as if it's buffering or in the process of rendering. I have to turn my phone off and many times reboot just to get it out of its ongoing loop. Even after reboot the app may fail to work correctly. I usually wait a few days to reopen it and it usually works normally. Besides a fix for that major bug, it would be really cool to have more completely manual features to set iso/aperture/shutter etc. and a lock to a set focus feature (like focus to infinity) which would all help greatly in shooting night time photography. The ability to use the macro and torch feature with the front camera would also open up some interesting possibilities. Even with the app getting a little buggy more often than not, it's still a brilliant application and tool. Props to the developers, especially those responsible for a couple of the mind blowing, seeminly physics defying filters!! Thank you for this great (and hopefully bug free) app.

One might think that an app that offers so much would come at a steep  price; however, one would be wrong! Every chance I get, I tell friends, colleagues, and students those were the best $2.99 I ever spent!  Even the free version offers the user a huge arsenal of camera and editing tools.
